## Root Cause Analysis

The `TypeError: Cannot read properties of null (reading 'map')` has **two contributing factors**:

### Primary Cause: Incorrect API Response Destructuring

In `src/stores/userStore.ts`, after yesterday's API migration:
```typescript
// BROKEN - accessing .users on an array
set({ users: response.data?.users ?? null, loading: false });
```

The new API format returns users directly in `data`:
```typescript
// The actual shape is:
// response = { data: [user1, user2, ...], meta: { total: 10 } }
// NOT { data: { users: [...] } }
```

So `response.data?.users` is always `undefined`, falling back to `null`.

### Secondary Cause: Null Initialization

```typescript
users: null  // Crashes if component renders before data loads
```

### Fix

**`src/stores/userStore.ts`:**
```typescript
// 1. Initialize as empty array
users: [],

// 2. Fix the destructuring
set({ users: response.data ?? [], loading: false });
```

**`src/components/UserList.tsx` (defensive):**
```typescript
{(users ?? []).map((user: User) => (
```

This ensures the component never crashes, even if the store has unexpected state.
